text: Keros () is a rural locality (a settlement) in Ust-Chernovskoye Rural Settlement, Gaynsky District, Perm Krai, Russia. The population was 568 as of 2010. There are 15 streets. == Geography == It is located 175 km north-west from Gayny. == References == Category:Rural localities in Gaynsky District
title: Keros, Perm Krai
